<subSubSection id="C3616545FFCCFF8CFF5E14B1FE17FDED" pageId="12" pageNumber="599" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC436CEFFCCFF8CFF5E14B1FE17FDED" blockId="12.[151,1127,449,697]" pageId="12" pageNumber="599">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFCCFF8CFF5E14B1FED8FE4D" bold="true" box="[151,262,449,473]" pageId="12" pageNumber="599">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is characterised by the unicolorous whitish elytra, long head with a largely elevated vertex, elevated medial lobe of pronotal disc and the flattened and shortened MT 2. Excepting of the shape of MT 2 being similar to males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFCCFF8CFCEA1772FBBDFD8D" authority="(Leconte, 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Leconte" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[803,1123,513,537]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFCCFF8CFCEA1772FCE7FD8D" box="[803,825,514,537]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="599">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFCCFF8CFC8D1772FC6BFD8D" box="[836,949,514,537]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="599">flavipennis</emphasis>
(Leconte, 1866)
</taxonomicName>
, in which MT 2 is cylindrical and as long as MT 3. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFCCFF8CFD641752FC6AFDAD" baseAuthorityName="Leconte" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[685,948,546,569]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFCCFF8CFD641752FC6AFDAD" box="[685,948,546,569]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="599">Macrosiagon flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in the New World from the 
<collectingCountry id="F36C765EFFCCFF8CFE5E1731FE3EFDCD" box="[407,480,577,601]" name="United States of America" pageId="12" pageNumber="599">U.S.A.</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B3FFFCCFF8CFE251731FDADFDCD" author="RIVNAY E." box="[492,627,577,601]" pageId="12" pageNumber="599" pagination="1 - 68" refId="ref30363" refString="RIVNAY E. 1929: Revision of the Ripiphoridae of North and Central America (Coleoptera). Memoirs of the American Entomological Society 6: 1 - 68, 4 pl." type="journal article" year="1929">RIVNAY 1929</bibRefCitation>
) through 
<collectingCountry id="F36C765EFFCCFF8CFD1E1731FCF6FDCD" box="[727,808,577,601]" name="Mexico" pageId="12" pageNumber="599">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B3FFFCCFF8CFCFC1731FC06FDCD" author="CHAMPION G. C." box="[821,984,577,601]" pageId="12" pageNumber="599" refId="ref28218" refString="CHAMPION G. C. 1891: Biologia Centrali-Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. IV (2). Heteromera (part). Taylor and Francis, London, [x] + 494 pp., 21 pls." type="book" year="1891">CHAMPION 1891</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<collectingCountry id="F36C765EFFCCFF8CFC341731FBB8FDCD" box="[1021,1126,577,601]" name="Argentina" pageId="12" pageNumber="599">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B3FFFCCFF8CFF561711FE63FDED" author="MANFRINI DE BREWER M." box="[159,445,609,633]" pageId="12" pageNumber="599" pagination="5 - 53" refId="ref29403" refString="MANFRINI DE BREWER M. 1966: Subfamilia Ripiphorinae (Col. Ripiphoridae) revision de las especies Argentinas del genero Macrosiagon Hentz. Revista de la Facultad de Ciencias Exactas, Fisicas y Naturales 27: 5 - 53." type="journal article" year="1966">MANFRINI DE BREWER 1966</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
